Germany Pledges $20 Million for Climate Assistance to Mali, Grenada

-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 
2011-12-06T08:50:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/germany-pledges-20-million-for-climate-assistance-to-mali-grenada.html
Germany pledged 15 million euros ($20
million) in funds to help two western Africa and Caribbean
countries cope with the effects of climate change.  Environment Minister Norbert Roettgen at UN climate talks
in  South Africa  pledged 10 million euros and 5 million euros,
respectively, to the governments of Mali and  Grenada , his
ministry said today in an e-mailed statement.  The money will be used to fund natural resource management
projects, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
 snicola2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  